decks.notes: The deck focuses on disrupting the opponent's strategy and controlling the game through counterspells, removal spells, and card advantage. It utilizes powerful artifacts and spells to control the board and manipulate the opponent's resources. The inclusion of Lurrus of the Dream-Den as a companion adds resiliency and flexibility to the deck's game plan. With a mix of efficient creatures, disruptive spells, and powerful mana acceleration, Esper Control aims to outlast and outmaneuver its opponents in order to secure victory.

This aggressive deck utilizes hatebears to disrupt the opponent's game plan while deploying threats of their own. With cards like Chancellor of the Annex and Archon of Emeria, the deck aims to slow down the opponent's spells while Seasoned Dungeoneer and White Plume Adventurer provide card advantage. The deck also includes powerful mana acceleration with cards like Black Lotus and Moxen to quickly get ahead of the opponent. By combining disruptive creatures with efficient mana production, this deck aims to overpower the opponent and secure victory in a fast-paced Vintage 1 vs 1 format.
